RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 72. Maiden Claiming Purse 35000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD FOALED IN NEW YORK STATE AND APPROVED BY THE NEW YORK STATE-BRED REGISTRY. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BONANA FANNA FOE was well placed behind the leading trio under urging, started the turn in the two path, shifted three then four wide while gaining later on that bend, closed fast to blow by the embattled leaders coming to the quarter-pole then went clear, drifted in significantly while having the rider fumble the crop in upper stretch, regained a hold of the crop while widening near the furlong marker, was flagged with the crop from the right-side once and proved much the best under a solid hand-ride to the wire. SARAH'S PRIDE bobbed her head while restless in the gate, bumped with a rival at the start then was taken up badly, spotted the front several lengths, went around the turn in the two path, turned into upper stretch in the three path and improved for the place. WINE GODDESS was urged along off the pace, moved from the two path to the four path around the turn, spun five wide into the stretch and weakened while clear for the show. FRANNIE LEW bumped with a foe at the start, showed speed under some restraint early, moved up to dispute the pace between horses, vied in the two path around the turn and tired. TAKE CHARGE LISA broke out from the outside post, contested the pace on the outside of two opponents, vied in the three path around the turn and capitulated. RENT CONTROL broke out at the start, showed good speed, disputed the pace on the inside of two foes, vied along the rail early on the turn, dropped back with three furlongs to run and stopped.

ENTRY.OWNER: Huber John M and Freed Thomas M
ENTRY.COMMENT: urged along, 2-4path turn, weakened, clear for show

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 71. Claiming Purse 28000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since July 1 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Wi ll Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: R GIRL FAITH coaxed from the gate, chased three then two wide coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, went six wide into upper stretch, rallied to take command three-sixteenths from home, then edged clear under a drive to prevail. SWEET SENSATION coaxed from the start, chased five paths off the inside down the backstretch and then just off the inside through the turn coming under coaxing at the seven-sixteenths, continued just off the inside for home, proved no match for the top one while running on well clear of the rest to be along second best. WICKED LADY six paths off the inside in closest aim of the leader, tucked four wide and advanced on that rival to take narrow command five-sixteenths from home, swung five wide into upper stretch under threat, yielded the front at the three-sixteenths and weakened to the finish while along for the show honors. SWEET SUGAR BABY hustled from the gate, chased just off the inside until tipped three wide at the nine-sixteenths, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, went five to six wide into upper stretch and weakened. CRYSTAL ORB coaxed from the gate, chased along the inside under a ride from the three-eighths, spun just off the inside for home and tired. ICE COLD GOLD established the front and showed the way in hand four then three wide coming under threat midway on the turn and was put to coaxing in response, yielded command with five-sixteenths to run, spun three wide into upper stretch and folded.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 44000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 1 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000 (Maiden And Claiming Races For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CONFIRMED GENIUS tracked the pace on the outside, chased in the four path around the turn, gained to make a bid before the furlong marker, took the lead approaching the sixteenth-pole and proved best under strong handling. OLIVE KAT moved around just prior to the start and broke a bit awkwardly, went up to show the way down the backstretch, vied in the three path around the turn, led under a drive until just before the sixteenth-pole then was overtaken while able to hold the place. CHLOE ROSE showed speed on the inside of a foe then between rivals, vied in the two path while between horses on the turn, dropped back at the five-sixteenths, kept on well in pursuit of the top two in the stretch and secured the show. BACI pressed the pace inside of foes down the backstretch, vied along the rail on the turn, dropped back at the five-sixteenths, kept on in the stretch but lacked the needed kick. PRAIRIE FIRE showed early speed, dropped back under urging late on the backstretch, went two then three wide around the turn, came five wide into the stretch then moved further out and lacked the needed response. GREATEST LOVE settled off the pace, was urged three then four wide around the turn, came six wide into the stretch and failed to respond.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 4 7F Dirt CR: 90. Starter Allowance Purse 55000. (UP TO $9,570 NYSBFOA) FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN OR CLAIMING. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 1 Allowed 3 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RUSSIAN TO WIN five wide in pursuit down the backstretch and through the turn, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, went seven wide into upper stretch, had the leader drift out in front and floated out two additional paths straightened away while rallying to collar that rival a furlong from home, then edged clear under a drive kept to task. BIG VENEZUELA coaxed from the gate, chased four wide in aim of the front advancing into the turn to apply pressure midway, took over command near the quarter pole and swung six wide for home, floated out two paths straightened away while under a drive and growing threat to the outside, got collared a furlong from home, dug in and ran on to preserve the place honors over a pair on the wire. LABARDE four then three wide in pursuit, came under coaxing at the seven-sixteenths, angled five wide for home, offered up a bid a furlong out, then kept on to the finish to secure the show honors in a photo with a pair. DOCTOR LOVE chased two to three wide until tucked inside half a mile from home, came under coaxing near the quarter pole and angled four wide into upper stretch, offered up a bid a furlong out, then kept on to the finish. ONE WHIRLWIND RIDE three wide in pursuit in closest aim of the leader, got coaxed along three furlongs from home, angled six wide into upper stretch and tired. FENWAY coaxed from the gate, showed the way just off the inside through swift splits, came under coaxing under challenge at the five-sixteenths, yielded command swinging three wide at the quarter pole and tired.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 57. Maiden Claiming Purse 35000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD FOALED IN NEW YORK STATE AND APPROVED BY THE NEW YORK STATE-BRED REGISTRY. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRETTY MISS KEENS was hustled from the start, sped clear while angling towards the inside, was challenged at the half-mile pole, vied inside of a foe while two to three wide around the turn, dueled with that foe until just before the sixteenth-pole then moved clear under steady handling. FOREVER AMY was hustled from the gate, moved up then was taken in hand near the nine-sixteenths, made a bid at the half-mile pole, vied outside of the winner in the three to four path around the turn, dueled with that foe until near the sixteenth-pole then was outfinished while just able to get the place. STRANGE FRUIT broke a bit slow, was urged along towards the rear, dropped from the two path to the rail around the turn, gained in the final furlong and finished willingly to just miss the place while clear for the show. K D KAKES broke a step slow, was urged along off the pace, went four wide on the turn, came five wide into the stretch and lacked the needed response. JOEYBIGNOSE was urged along off the pace, dropped back leaving the backstretch, raced inside to the two path around the turn and failed to rally. MAGNOLIA WIND was off a bit slow, moved out while urged along, went three then four wide on the turn, spun six wide into the stretch and failed to threaten. BRITNEY IS FREE broke a step slow, was urged along on the outside, dropped from the four path to the two path early on the turn and was no factor. BETTING ON A STONE was hustled from the start then urged along off the pace, dropped back leaving the backstretch, went three wide around the turn and failed to respond.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 36000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 1 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SIMPLE SUGAR chased three wide briefly before tipping out five then four wide down the backstretch, went four wide through the turn coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, angled six wide into upper stretch, dug in under a drive issuing a challenge through the final furlong and was just up in the last jump to score. NEW YORK SUPREME broke out at the start and was corrected, raced six to seven paths off the inside down the backstretch and then five wide through the turn, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, continued five wide into upper stretch, rallied to take command just inside the eighth pole, dug in under threat and was nailed in the shadow of the wire. FOCUS broke out at the start and was corrected, dueled four then three wide with HOLIDAY JAZZ to her inside, took over sole command at the five-sixteenths, swung three wide for home, dug in under threat and was collared just inside the eighth pole, ran on through to the finish to preserve the show honors. HOLIDAY JAZZ coaxed from the gate, dueled three then two wide with the aforementioned foe to her outside, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, swung four wide into upper stretch and ran on to the wire. FREUDIAN six paths off the inside down the backstretch, darted to the two path into the turn, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, went seven wide at the head of the stretch and offered no response. RICELLE five to six paths off the inside down the backstretch, tucked four wide through the turn coming under coaxing three furlongs from home, went seven wide at the top of the stretch and weakened.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 7 1 1/8M Dirt CR: 100. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 84000. (UP TO $14,616 NYSBFOA) FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $18,000 TWICE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER OR STATE BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $62,500. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners O f Two Races Other Than Claiming Or Starter At A Mile Or Over Since July 1 Allowed 3 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 5 lbs. Claiming Price $62,500 (Allowance Horses Preferred)(1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void) .
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NO BURN brushed with a foe early, dropped from the two path to the rail around the first turn, moved to the lead with six furlongs to run, showed the way down the backstretch, vied in the three path while under a bit of extra left-rein pressure around the far turn, spun four wide into the stretch then drifted out while clear and drew away under steady urging. LITTLE DEMON was hustled from the gate, showed the way in the two to three path around the early part of the opening bend, lost the lead to the winner with six furlongs to run, prompted that foe down the backstretch, chased inside to the two path around the final turn and safely secured the place. LOCALLY OWNED started the first turn in the two path, shifted three then four wide later on that bend, was forwardly placed on the outside down the backstretch, chased in the five path around the far turn, was driven six wide into upper stretch and weakened but held the show. BE BETTER brushed with a rival into the first turn, rounded that bend in the four path, settled at the rear, moved from the rail to the three path around the far turn, came four wide into the stretch, drifted out near the sixteenth-pole and failed to threaten. TWO THIRTY FIVE went three to four wide on the first turn, raced just off the pace, chased in the four path around the far the far turn, spun five wide into the stretch and came up empty. SENIOR INVESTMENT brushed with a foe into the first turn, moved from three to five wide around that bend, was urged along on the backstretch, traveled three wide on the far turn and was no factor.
